description:
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Qualified Nursing Associate to join our team on Lancaster Ward at Lincoln county hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lancaster ward is a 20 bedded ward. We specialise in healthcare for the older person,. We look after patients with complex needs, with a range of specialties within that. We have a particular passion for Dementia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lancaster is passionate about delivering high standards of care to the patients that are admitted to the ward, catering for their needs on an individual basis. The successful candidate will receive training and support to enable you to deliver the high quality care that our patients require.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working alongside the ward sister and the deputy sisters health care of the older person has a clinical educator to support the training needs of all staff working within health care of the older person. We also have a dementia practioner working closely with us, and a clinical nurse specialist for frailty.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team are highly skilled and motivated, and keen to develop further. This role is for a trained nursing associate with the skills to be able to manage the busy workload of the ward and to be keen to learn new skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameKarin WistowJob titleWard SisterEmail addresskarin.wistow@ulh.nhs.ukTelephone number01522 597707Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
